-aragir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 1501<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/22/02 7:48:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16053.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: banishing</span><hr size=1> I was under the impression the Warrior's AE Taunt always worked and never failed.  I'd have to be a Warrior to know for sure though. ^_^<br>
<br>
Procing agro reduction I believe is an interesting and good thing Verant added to the game.  It is a great way to change monster behavior without adding a bunch of complex API and also has a tendance to break classic MT style encounters.  It simulates the &quot;oh, I'm attacking a Warrior that did /disc defensive...I should switch targets&quot; kind of intelegence NPC monsters do desperately need.<br>
<br>
I've said before it would be a great leap forward in AI/challenge if the monsters acted more like players.  If they grouped together and semi-coordinated, perferenced attacking some targets over others(ie. going after healers first), and actually could escape (escape meaning they &quot;got away&quot; but looses everyone's agro...a true draw) then I think some will like the challenge more than the 30 minutes fights they currently have geared. <p><font size="+1">
