</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/22/02 7:48:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 513<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/22/02 7:56:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16053.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zerging</span><hr size=1> They've already done the first two.  There are plenty of mobs that have weak resistances in one area and high resistances in the others.  We've seen the bane damage stuff in Luclin, so that would be nothing new, the downside is the timesink of getting the bane weapons.<br>
<br>
The immediate thing I see in the front/back damage only idea is that if you block off rear damage then you're in effect nerfing rogues for that encounter.  Not that it's necessarily a bad thing, since there are plenty of encounters where mobs are MR and certain casters can't do much, etc., but it's something to keep in mind.<br>
<br>
If you negated frontal damage that would probably be pretty chaotic.  Might be a perfect mob for a hybrid tank if you could land spells from the front, otherwise you'd probably have the mob ping-ponging around unless it was rootable or something.<br>
<br>
From what I've seen, it really seems like SOE is trying to create encounters where the MT concept won't work.  Banishing mobs, knockback mobs, DT mobs, it seems like all of those things are meant to make it harder to keep aggro on the same guy for the whole fight.  So far for most things it seems players are pretty creative in finding ways to make the MT concept work in spite of all that.  I'll bet people would come up with ways of making this encounter work too. <p><BR>
